om/users/martinwicke/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}], "milestone": null, "comments": 0, "created_at": "2018-04-16T19:29:30Z", "updated_at": "2018-04-16T21:36:02Z", "closed_at": "2018-04-16T21:25:17Z", "author_association": "MEMBER", "pull_request": {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/tensorflow/tensorflow/pulls/18570", "html_url": "https://github.com/tensorflow/tensorflow/pull/18570", "diff_url": "https://github.com/tensorflow/tensorflow/pull/18570.diff", "patch_url": "https://github.com/tensorflow/tensorflow/pull/18570.patch"}, "body_html": "<p>While revisiting <a class=\"issue-link js-issue-link\" data-error-text=\"Failed to load issue title\" data-id=\"309948913\" data-permission-text=\"Issue title is private\" data-url=\"https://github.com/tensorflow/tensorflow/issues/18106\" data-hovercard-type=\"pull_request\" data-hovercard-url=\"/tensorflow/tensorflow/pull/18106/hovercard\" href=\"https://github.com/tensorflow/tensorflow/pull/18106\">#18106</a> I noticed that Bahdanau attention has a similar dtype mismatch issue when normalized=True. The issue comes from:</p>\n<pre><code>     g = variable_scope.get_variable(\n         \"attention_g\", dtype=dtype,\n         initializer=math.sqrt((1. / num_units)))\n</code></pre>\n<p>where the initializer value does not work well with differnt dtype.</p>\n<p>This fix converts changes the initializer to <code>init_ops.constant_initializer</code><br>\nto address the issue, and adds additional test cases for it.</p>\n<p>Signed-off-by: Yong Tang <a href=\"mailto:yong.tang.github@outlook.com\">yong.tang.github@outlook.com</a></p>", "body_text": "While revisiting #18106 I noticed that Bahdanau attention has a similar dtype mismatch issue when normalized=True. The issue comes from:\n     g = variable_scope.get_variable(\n         \"attention_g\", dtype=dtype,\n         initializer=math.sqrt((1. / num_units)))\n\nwhere the initializer value does not work well with differnt dtype.\nThis fix converts changes the initializer to init_ops.constant_initializer\nto address the issue, and adds additional test cases for it.\nSigned-off-by: Yong Tang yong.tang.github@outlook.com", "body": "While revisiting #18106 I noticed that Bahdanau attention has a similar dtype mismatch issue when normalized=True. The issue comes from:\r\n```\r\n     g = variable_scope.get_variable(\r\n         \"attention_g\", dtype=dtype,\r\n         initializer=math.sqrt((1. / num_units)))\r\n```\r\nwhere the initializer value does not work well with differnt dtype.\r\n\r\nThis fix converts changes the initializer to `init_ops.constant_initializer`\r\nto address the issue, and adds additional test cases for it.\r\n\r\nSigned-off-by: Yong Tang <yong.tang.github@outlook.com>\r\n"}